Text: Great, the next part :D Thank you for this. I've been checking every day for part 11. I was just about to go to bed now, luckily I remembered to check.

So was I.
Allelujah !
Thanks agains for your wonderfull job.
All this music is not dead you make it living.
Thanks again
Wow, yet another! Very impressive series this. Please keep them coming - thanks a lot!!
Again, you are the man! Thank you 10000 times SpandauBaby!
SpandauBaby, Just wanted to say thank you for this great collection. This is awesome! Can't wait for the other parts.

Another fantastic effort. Thankyou so much Spandaubaby. This is the first part of the collection where I have never heard of any of the artists before, so I'm really looking forward to hearing this!

Again, I hope you appreciate how much we are all enjoying this and how much we appreciate your efforts. Here's to part 12 and "J" !
thanks so much for your ourstanding collection. me and some of my friends are delighted hearing "the old stuff" again..

Thanks again SB. I am fairly lacking in Italian bands so this should prove beneficial. I wonder if there is any from the orient like Japan et al or the Latino world available. It seems like they do not stay seeded long so I can only hope to hear them one day. I think I got one album from Spain from the seventies, but they just weren't available. Come on you worlders, educate us with your progressive rythyms! Pleeaasse.
You make me smile on the way to work

love it all (well, I'm not into the jazz fusion & symphonic prog:  could never get into that stuff, don't know why)

but these are seeding well and on this part I'm really looking forward to Improve Sound Ltd albums.  I have never had anything complete.

cheers
